g.text: Default gain of INA is 2000X. Absolute accuracy of
INA internal resistors is 10X so need that much trim range.
conduct before INA internal diodes, and
form an RF low-pass filter with the capacitors.
Could add a ferrite bead as well but be careful
Low-leakage diodes protect INA inputs from
common mode voltages beyond the supply rails
and differential voltages above 1V. Can handle
500mA until they overheat or about 40V to GND
Zeners protect against input signal overvoltage
to the power rails through the protection diodes.
This journal article is relevant and may be freely accessible on Aug 18 2021:
"A low cost versatile differential preamplifier for electronic engineering"
